Five-seven IOM NEW IN BOX UNFIRED with everthing it was shipped with.
The Five-seven IOM (Individual Officer Model) was the first model of the Five-seven pistol to be offered to civilian shooters, debuting in 2004. It is now discontinued in favor of the USG model. The IOM was similar in its basic design to the Tactical version, but differed in that it had a MIL-STD-1913 (Picatinny) accessory rail, a serrated slide and trigger guard, and fully adjustable sights. It also had a magazine safety mechanism incorporated into the design, to prevent the pistol from being fired without a magazine inserted. title: For Sale:  Sir, you have crossed the line!!!
postcontent:
I was recently flagged by someone on this site as "Buyer beware", and "rude" For listing my Stoeger P350. This person/troll also accused me of being an irresponsible gun owner! Now keep in mind, this person was able to make this determination by me simply stating I was firm on price, and would not accept $300 when I was asking $450. 

For those of us who have had more than one transaction on this great site, the good out weighs the crack pots.
I have conducted numerous transactions trading/buying/ selling with fellow enthusiasts on Armslist without one issue or complaint of " being rude", or disrespectful. 

However, I will not accept or tolerate for someone to call me a "irresponsible gun owner" because I would not reply to:
" I know your gun is worth $400, I will give you $150 cash"
" I have a Jennings .25 with uncle miles holster trade you even"
"Trade you my Seiko, needs battery"
" Poulan chainsaw"

So, to all of you that did not get a response from the above. Oh well...
Also, to the guy who texted me 10 times to meet you at 5:00 pm at Walmart, I waited 
20 minutes!! Oh well...  
Also, the guy who drove 45 minutes to meet me, and refused to sign a bill, I know you were pissed, all you had to do was sign it, or show me your HCP. Oh well...

"Buyer beware" right... we should start a post "seller beware" of trolls like yourself.
Our rights are sacred and being questioned daily. 
People like you who cry foul for no reason need to stay to the left, or go troll Craigslist for things that go bang.

I will be contacting and forwarding the relplies to the moderators.

title: For Sale:  Gary Reeder Wyoming Hunter 307 GNR Single Action
postcontent: The 307 GNR is based on the 357 Maximum case necked down to 7mm and 30 caliber. I have done extensive testing with the 307 GNR and it performs flawlessly. The 284 GNR works fine, but some of the shorter lighter weight 7mm bullets are hard to find these days so only preliminary testing has been done on it. As more and more 7mm bullets become available I will be doing more testing on it. The 307 GNR will be a bit more power than the 300 GNR plus you don't have to do the cutting, trimming and such that is required on the 300 GNR. The downside is that a Ruger stretch frame revolver is required for the conversion. The good thing is that the Ruger 357 Maximum revolvers are easier to get and cheaper than in recent past.
